Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "drag" in different forms and positions:

1. *Drag* mi je što sam se upoznao sa tobom. (I'm glad that I've met you.)
2. Kupio sam *dragi* poklon za svoju devojku. (I bought a precious gift for my girlfriend.)
3. *Drago* mi je što si se vratio kući. (I'm happy that you've returned home.)
4. Ona je *drag* prijatelj. (She's a dear friend.)
5. *Draga* moja, kako si provela dan? (My dear, how was your day?)
6. Njen osmeh mi je veoma *drag*. (Her smile is very dear to me.)
7. Ovo je vrlo *dragocena* informacija. (This is a very valuable information.)
8. *Dragulj* je bio ukraden iz muzeja. (The jewel was stolen from the museum.)
9. On je *dragan* čovek, ali ponekad ume da bude i težak. (He's a lovable person, but sometimes he can be difficult.)
10. *Dragocene* uspomene će ostati zauvek. (Precious memories will stay forever.)

Note: I've put an asterisk (*) right after the word "drag" in each sentence for easier identification.